---
<Layout
  title="About Us — Raising Impact"
  active="about"
  description="Learn about RaisingImpact.Org (RIO) — our mission, founding team, and rigorous methodology for maximising philanthropic capital across India and Asia. Inspired by Founders Pledge and GiveWell."
  keywords="About Raising Impact, RIO founding team, philanthropy India, Vikrant Bhargava, Luke Ding, Rukmini Pandit, ECCE research, effective philanthropy"
>
  <section class="page-header" id="top">
    <h1>Raising Impact</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Guiding Philanthropy With Rigour</p>
    <hr class="page-header-divider" />
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="section-container">
      <p>Raising Impact acts as a strategic bridge between three pillars: intentional philanthropists, expert implementers, and the existing body of evidence. Rather than prescribing priorities, we meet the ecosystem where it is. We provide structured, context-sensitive advisory, grounded in rigorous research and sector expertise, to ensure philanthropic capital reaches its most effective destination. Our mission is simple: to maximize the impact of every dollar spent.</p>
      <p>Raising Impact undertakes rigorous cause-area research, conducts state-level and sector-level analyses, engages subject-matter experts and on-ground organisations, and applies structured processes to evaluate the cost-effectiveness and scalability of interventions. Drawing on global models such as <a href="https://www.founderspledge.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Founders Pledge</a> and <a href="https://www.givewell.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GiveWell</a>, Raising Impact adapts these analytical frameworks to the Indian context, intending to expand across Asia.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section alt">
    <div class="section-container">
      <h2>Our Journey So Far</h2>
      <p>We began with a pilot research study in Early Childhood Care &amp; Education (ECCE). The team mapped sector needs, capital flows, effective interventions, and credible nonprofits across India. Findings included a 17x impact multiple for Anganwadi (child care centres) capacity-building and Maharashtra’s (Indian state) paradox of high CSR funding but poor child well-being outcomes.</p>
      <p>Building on this momentum, we initiated a strategic engagement with an independent philanthropist in August 2025 to enhance incomes of marginal and smallholder farmers. We focused on horticulture, high-value crops, and allied sectors as the most effective pathways, and, to address the lack of rigorous sector evidence, designed a targeted four-stage grant call to identify mid-sized NGOs with cost-effective interventions in high-priority states.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="how-we-work-section">
    <div class="section-container">
      <h2>How We Work</h2>
      <div class="hww-grid">
        <div class="hww-item">
          <span class="hww-number">01</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="hww-title">Cause Area Research</h3>
            <p class="hww-desc">State and sector analyses to target high-impact philanthropy</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hww-item">
          <span class="hww-number">02</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="hww-title">Expert Engagement</h3>
            <p class="hww-desc">Experts and field partners validate research, implementation fidelity and feasibility</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hww-item">
          <span class="hww-number">03</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="hww-title">Structured Evaluation</h3>
            <p class="hww-desc">Cost-effectiveness analysis using adapted GiveWell and Founders Pledge methods</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hww-item">
          <span class="hww-number">04</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="hww-title">Capital Deployment</h3>
            <p class="hww-desc">Donors matched with vetted, deployment-ready organisations</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section alt">
    <div class="section-container">
      <h2>Why Partner With Us?</h2>
      <table class="partner-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Feature</th>
            <th>Philanthropic Benefit</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Vetted Pipeline</td>
            <td>Pre-screened, high-fidelity organizations ready for capital</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Shared Expertise</td>
            <td>Benefit from the collective intelligence of Sattva Consulting and Veddis Foundation</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Measurable RoI</td>
            <td>Confidence that your capital is linked to data-backed, scalable outcomes.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section alt">
    <div class="section-container">
      <h2>Our Team</h2>
      <p>The RIO team brings together decades of experience across Indian philanthropy, public policy, nonprofit operations, and sector research. We combine:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Analytical depth</li>
        <li>On-ground understanding</li>
        <li>Strong regional insight</li>
        <li>A commitment to evidence and measurable outcomes</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Collaboration is at the heart of our work—whether with philanthropists, NGOs, state governments, or peer research organisations.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="team-section">
    <div class="section-container">
      <h2 style="color: var(--darkest-navy); font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--rich-gold); padding-left: 1rem;">Founding Team</h2>
      <div class="team-grid">
        {team.map((member) => (
          <div class="team-card">
            <img class="team-photo" src={member.img} alt={member.name} loading="lazy" />
            <p class="name">{member.name}</p>
            <a class="team-linkedin" href={member.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label={`${member.name} on LinkedIn`}>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="18" height="18" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M20.45 20.45h-3.55v-5.57c0-1.33-.03-3.04-1.85-3.04-1.85 0-2.13 1.44-2.13 2.94v5.67H9.36V9h3.41v1.56h.05c.48-.9 1.64-1.85 3.38-1.85 3.61 0 4.28 2.38 4.28 5.47v6.27zM5.34 7.43a2.06 2.06 0 1 1 0-4.12 2.06 2.06 0 0 1 0 4.12zM7.12 20.45H3.56V9h3.56v11.45zM22.22 0H1.77C.79 0 0 .77 0 1.72v20.56C0 23.23.79 24 1.77 24h20.45c.98 0 1.78-.77 1.78-1.72V1.72C24 .77 23.2 0 22.22 0z"/>
              </svg>
              <span>LinkedIn</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="back-to-top-wrap">
    <a href="#top" class="back-to-top">Back To Top</a>
  </div>
</Layout>
